      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-cou2-equivalency-criteria",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between the computational model and the physical test confirmed through a structured parameter mapping table (report MCEQ-2025-010). Inlet velocity profiles extracted from PIV measurements and applied as boundary conditions in CFD; rotational speed set to tachometer-measured values; fluid properties (density, dynamic viscosity, non-Newtonian Carreau parameters) derived from rheometry measurements at 37 °C. Wall roughness (Ra = 0.8 μm) measured by profilometry and incorporated as equivalent sand-grain roughness. All parameters traceable to calibrated instruments with NIST-traceable calibration certificates. No unresolved parameter discrepancies identified."
    }
